cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.DL 

The paper discusses a study on how users re-find information, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study specifically focuses on re-finding information on the web, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of annotations as a means of adding context to aid in re-finding suggests a possible connection to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and deep learning (cs.DL) for improving the accuracy and efficiency of annotation-based re-finding.
